WEBVTT

00:00.163 --> 00:02.297
<i>This was your beat?</i>

00:03.278 --> 00:05.045
Yeah. Italian border,

00:05.080 --> 00:07.114
from here all the way
up to Switzerland.

00:07.149 --> 00:08.482
It's a hell of
a lot more picturesque

00:08.533 --> 00:09.900
than where I worked.

00:09.934 --> 00:12.770
Well, the longer
you police an area,

00:12.804 --> 00:13.804
the harder it is

00:13.839 --> 00:15.005
to appreciate picturesque.

00:15.040 --> 00:17.825
Lot of human-trafficking
through here?

00:17.876 --> 00:18.926
More all the time.

00:18.960 --> 00:20.277
I was working on
a joint operation,

00:20.312 --> 00:22.146
with some of
the other border regions.

00:22.180 --> 00:23.814
I'd like to see
that investigation

00:23.849 --> 00:26.333
if you still have access.

00:26.368 --> 00:28.419
That's why
you asked me to bring you

00:28.453 --> 00:30.037
to my old stomping grounds?

00:30.088 --> 00:31.755
It's related
to Phillip Genovese,

00:31.790 --> 00:33.874
the files you had me gather?

00:33.909 --> 00:35.993
It may have something
to do with Genovese.

00:36.011 --> 00:37.294
I don't know.

00:37.328 --> 00:38.379
But I really do want to
familiarize myself

00:38.430 --> 00:39.947
with the area.

00:39.981 --> 00:42.900
I guess I could
introduce you to Captain Geroux,

00:42.934 --> 00:45.335
my former superior.

00:45.353 --> 00:48.171
And I wouldn't mind checking up
on the progress myself.

00:48.190 --> 00:50.173
Great.

00:51.309 --> 00:52.893
You mean now, don't you?

